===Kuwait===
The Kuwaiti Maritime Museum in Salmiya, Kuwait, holds replicas of a number of different types of dhows. The &quot;Al-Hashemi-II&quot; (1997-2001), in Kuwait City, Kuwait, was recognized by Guinness World Records as the largest wooden dhow ever built; it has never been floated and is used for events. These do not seem to qualify as historic ships preserved in museums so they are not listed here.

